CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 15, 1957, pg. 14 reads: "Winners - All three of these charming women were winners when the total raised by Victory Charity Club members was announced at the annual tea. The huge amount was $1,454.41.  Mrs. Margaret Washington, left, raised $655; Mrs. Mozelle Moore, center, reported $715, thereby making her "Miss Victory" for 1957.  At right, Mrs. Viola Sams, founder-president, congratulates the pair, knowing that their efforts and those of other club members would carry on the Victory Charity Club's charitable program for the years. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Victory Charity Club members Margaret Washington, Mozelle Moore, and Viola Sams, shaking hands while standing in front of American flag in YMCA for annual tea
